    "created_at": "2026-03-19T00:00:00.000Z",
    "notes": "Iron Condor with defined risk. Strategy: (1) Sell 0.25 delta CE+PE, buy 0.10 delta wings for protection. (2) Max loss is capped at wing-to-short spread width minus premium collected. (3) Profit target: 60% of premium — statistically the sweet spot before gamma risk explodes. (4) Rolls the breached side completely (short+wing together) to maintain wing protection. (5) VIX-tightening rule opportunistically moves shorts to 0.30 delta when market is calm. (6) No entry on expiry day — gamma risk too high for condors. (7) Early EOD exit at 15:20 on expiry days."
